non tab non tabular data.

00:15:07.099 --> 00:15:10.599
It would be tricky from a from from a user interface standpoint

00:15:10.599 --> 00:15:14.299
because if it doesn't map into the it doesn't map neatly into

00:15:14.299 --> 00:15:14.799
the grid.

00:15:14.799 --> 00:15:19.500
We would need to develop some other type of UI layer that enables

00:15:19.500 --> 00:15:23.000
you to to drill down into the different.

00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:28.000
Let's say you were looking at a large nested dictionary type

00:15:28.000 --> 00:15:31.700
object or like a nested like a nested array like a NumPy array

00:15:31.700 --> 00:15:35.900
with more than two dimensions is is that type of thing?

00:15:35.900 --> 00:15:40.099
You can open our matrices in the data Explorer but dimensions

00:15:40.099 --> 00:15:40.599
more than that.

00:15:40.599 --> 00:15:42.400
We haven't we haven't built support yet.

00:15:42.400 --> 00:15:45.099
But if you have an idea of like how that how you think that that

00:15:45.099 --> 00:15:47.900
should work in the data Explorer would be interested in in

00:15:47.900 --> 00:15:48.500
hearing from you.

00:15:49.799 --> 00:15:50.299
Great.

00:15:52.500 --> 00:15:55.000
How well does the data viewer play with the dreaded list

00:15:55.000 --> 00:15:55.500
column?

00:16:01.700 --> 00:16:06.700
I I know that you can see I know that you can see list columns

00:16:07.299 --> 00:16:07.799
one.

00:16:07.799 --> 00:16:11.500
That's one area that we have not like it's it if you go on the

00:16:11.500 --> 00:16:15.400
positron issue tracker, there are issues about having improved

00:16:15.400 --> 00:16:21.200
UI for for list types and like looking at complex values.

00:16:21.200 --> 00:16:29.400
So for example, if you have a large value that does not fit in a

00:16:29.400 --> 00:16:31.099
that does not fit in a data cell.

00:16:32.400 --> 00:16:37.099
So, you know, we like for example, like if we had a value that

00:16:37.099 --> 00:16:39.700
doesn't fit here if you hover over it, it will show you a tool

00:16:39.900 --> 00:16:44.700
tip showing the whole value but for more complex objects, including

00:16:44.700 --> 00:16:45.799
list or array types.

00:16:45.799 --> 00:16:49.900
If you're using Polar's Polar's has a built-in list type, it will

00:16:49.900 --> 00:16:55.000
format the values as it will show the list of values within the

00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:59.400
cell, but we'd like to be able to drill into those those cells and

00:16:59.400 --> 00:17:03.700
get a richer UI display to be able to like similar to how you can

00:17:03.700 --> 00:17:07.400
look at a JavaScript object like a JSON object in the Chrome

00:17:07.400 --> 00:17:08.800
